**Operating modes:**

**Mode A – Separate service invoice**

For each customer involved in the ECS invoicing session who has valid recurring lines (with “Manage in ECS” = true and consistent validity dates):

* ECS generates a single, separate sales invoice containing exclusively the selected recurring lines
* The invoice is created only once per customer, even if in the same ECS session N merchandise invoices have been generated for the same “Bill-to”
* The recurring services invoice is counted in the total number of invoices created by the ECS session

**Mode B – Append to merchandise invoices**

For each customer for whom one or more merchandise invoices are created in the ECS session:

* ECS adds the valid recurring lines (with the “Manage in ECS” flag active) to the customer’s merchandise invoices
* In the case of multiple merchandise invoices generated for the same “Bill-to” (e.g. split by ship-to, reason code, etc.), the appending takes place on all invoices generated by ECS

**Note**: if a customer has no valid recurring lines, no separate services invoice is created.

